{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"linear"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore9AnimationV","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Animation","text":"Animation"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"return-value","level":2,"text":"Return Value","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A linear animation with the default duration."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A linear animation provides a mechanical feel to the motion because its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"speed is consistent from start to finish of the animation. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"constant speed makes a linear animation ideal for animating the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"movement of objects where changes in the speed might feel awkward, such","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as with an activity indicator.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following code shows an example of using linear animation to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"animate the movement of a circle as it moves between the leading and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"trailing edges of the view. The circle also animates its color change"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as it moves across the view."}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["struct ContentView: View {","    @State private var isActive = false","","    var body: some View {","        VStack(alignment: isActive ? .trailing : .leading) {","            Circle()","                .fill(isActive ? Color.red : Color.blue)","                .frame(width: 50, height: 50)","","            Button(\"Animate\") {","                withAnimation(.linear) {","                    isActive.toggle()","                }","            }","            .frame(maxWidth: .infinity)","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"linear"},{"type":"text","text":" animation has a default duration of 0.35 seconds. To"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specify a different duration, use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Animation\/linear(duration:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Animation"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/animation\/linear"]}],"metadata":{"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"linear"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore9AnimationV","text":"Animation"}],"platforms":[{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"iOS","introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false},{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"10.15","unavailable":false},{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"tvOS","introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false},{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"visionOS","introducedAt":"1.0","unavailable":false},{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"watchOS","introducedAt":"6.0","unavailable":false}],"role":"symbol